headline: Archer Aviation Joins White House Flying Taxi Program
summary: Archer Aviation Inc. (NYSE:ACHR) shares traded higher on Monday after the company announced on Friday that it will join the White House's new electric vertical takeoff and landing aircraft program. The initiative, aimed at speeding the rollout of flying taxis, will see Archer collaborate with airlines and U.S. cities to design and conduct trial operations. The program, known as the eVTOL Integration Pilot Program (eIPP), was created by an executive order signed by President Donald Trump in June.

headline: Wall Street All But Abandons Its Trade Angst as Rate Cuts Near
summary: The S&P 500 Index has surged 32% since President Donald Trump first outlined his onslaught of global levies in April, with most forecasters expecting further gains before year-end.  While Trump’s tariffs weigh on business confidence and are slowly creeping into consumer prices, Wall Street is acutely focused on the Fed’s path for borrowing costs and continued enthusiasm around artificial intelligence to keep the S&P 500 rally afloat.
